'''Ahmed Skirej''' (also transcribed '''Skiredj''') or '''Abu-l-Abbas Ahmed ibn al-Iyyashi Sukayrij al-Khazraji Al-Ansari al-Fasi''' (1878-1944) was a well known Moroccan Sufi scholar and judge.<ref>Temsamani, Abdelaziz Khalouk, "Hayât al-qâdî Ahmad Skîrj wa âthâruhu" (Vie et œuvre d'Ahmed Skirej:1878-1944), ''Majallat dâr an-niyâba'' 9 (1986), pp. 49-57</ref> He wrote a great number of books, but is especially well known for his voluminous work on the companions of [[Ahmad al-Tijani|Sidi Ahmad al-Tijani]]: ''Kitab kashf al-Hijab ámman talaaqa bi-Shaykh Tijani mina-l As'hab'' (Raising the veil of the companions who encountered Sheikh Tijani).
