'''Johan Frans Podolyn''' or '''Johann Franz Podolyn''' ([[Lisbon]] 29 May 1739 - [[Gothenburg]] 29 May 1784)<ref>''Bulletin de l'Institut fondamental de l'Afrique noire: Sciences naturelles'' Volume 35 (1973) [https://books.google.com/books?ei=mbThTLXmLcaycIK0sZcM&ct=result&id=GbI_AAAAYAAJ&dq=Johan+Podolyn+est+mort+le+jour+de+son&q=PODOLYN%2C+n%C3%A9+%C3%A0+Lisbonne+le+29+mai+1739%2C+est+mort+%C3%A0+G%C3%B4teborg+le+jour+de+son+45e+anniversaire%2C+le+29+mai+1784.#search_anchor p. 549] {{fr icon}}</ref><ref name=Minnespenningar207>"Johan Frans Podolijn", Emil Hildebrand, ''Minnespenningar öfver enskilda svenska män och qvinnor'', Stockholm : Kongl. Witterhets Historie och Antiqvitets Akademiens Förlag, 1860, OCLC 457966652, [https://books.google.com/books?id=SBQXAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA153&dq=Johan+Frans+Podolijn&hl=en&ei=A4TlTJ7DJoewcf7hqc0K&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=i%20Lisabon%20d.%2029%20Maj&f=false p. 207] {{sv icon}}</ref> was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] [[numismatics|numismatist]] who published on [[Cyrenaic coins of Corvo|Punic currency]] in his possession which had been found on the [[Corvo Island|island of Corvo]] in the [[Azores Islands|Azores]]. He wrote about the discovery in 1778 in a Swedish academic publication now known as the Publications of the [[Royal Society of Sciences and Letters in Gothenburg]], presumably indicating that he was a member of the society.<ref>"Några Anmärkingnar om de Gamles Sjöfart, i anledning af några Carthaginensiska och Cyrenaiska Mynt, fundne år 1749, på en af de Azoriska Öarne", af Johan Podolyn, ''Det Götheborgska Wetenskaps och Witterhets Samhallets Handlinger Wetenskaps Afdelningen,'' Först Stycket, 1778. Facsimile of first page at Richard Hennig, ''Terrae Incognitae: Eine Zusammenstellung und kritische Bewertung der wichtigsten vorkolumbischen Entdeckungsreisen an Hand der darüber vorliegenden Originalberichte'', 4 vols., repr. Leiden: Brill, 1944, OCLC 459874588, [https://books.google.com/books?id=S8MUAAAAIAAJ&pg=PA139&dq=Johan+Podolyn&hl=en&ei=vlzkTPX7IIHvcPmhgbIM&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=6&ved=0CDoQ6AEwBTgK#v=onepage&q=Johan%20Podolyn&f=false p. 140] (Book in German)</ref><ref>John Murray, ''Selections from Report on the Scientific Results of the Voyage of H.M.S. Challenger During the Years 1872-76'', New York: Arno, 1977, {{ISBN|0-405-10411-1}}, [https://books.google.com/books?id=kxJvRib3-ggC&pg=PA2&dq=Johan+Podolyn&hl=en&ei=mrHhTIzlJY_QccH34JcM&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCcQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Johan%20Podolyn&f=false p. 2, note 3] slightly misspells the title of the report.</ref>
Podolyn was the son of a Swedish merchant and Vice-Consul. He had a gift for languages and worked for the [[Jonas Alströmer|Alströmer]] family, accompanying them on voyages<ref>Stig Rydén, ''The Banks Collection: An Episode in 18th-Century Anglo-Swedish Relations'', Stockholm: Almqvist & Wiksell, 1963, OCLC 3268710, [https://books.google.com/books?ei=vlzkTPX7IIHvcPmhgbIM&ct=result&id=UYMbAAAAIAAJ&dq=Johan+Podolyn&q=A+gifted+linguist%2C+Johann+Podolyn+entered+service+with+the#search_anchor p. 52, note 1].</ref> in addition to working as a bookkeeper in [[Gothenburg]] and [[Alingsås]].<ref name=Minnespenningar207/> He amassed a considerable coin collection.<ref name=Berg>Wilhelm Berg, ''Anteckningar om Göteborgs äldre teatrar'' Volume 1 ''1690 - 1794'', Göteborg Boktryckeri, 1896, OCLC 218053709, [https://books.google.com/books?id=STtBAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA123&dq=Johan+Frans+Podolijn&hl=en&ei=A4TlTJ7DJoewcf7hqc0K&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4&ved=0CDQQ6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=Johan%20Frans%20Podolijn&f=false p. 123] {{sv icon}}</ref> He was married to Anna Norberg;<ref name=Berg/> he had been engaged to marry Jeanette Ölander, but she died before the marriage could take place.<ref>"Jeanette Ölander", Hildebrand, [https://books.google.com/books?id=SBQXAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA153&dq=Johan+Frans+Podolijn&hl=en&ei=A4TlTJ7DJoewcf7hqc0K&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDAQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&q=Johan%20Frans%20Podolijn&f=false p. 206].</ref>
